</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Sep 2013 22:52:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">http://nwazet.com:80/camera-bundle</guid></item><item><title>Nwazet Pi Minitux Case Hempfest Limited Edition</title><link>http://nwazet.com:80/minitux-hempfest</link><description>&lt;p&gt;The Hempfest Minitux is a beautiful, limited edition, acrylic case. 
We designed it exclusively for &lt;a href="https://www.hempfest.org/"&gt;Hempfest 2013&lt;/a&gt; to commemorate the legalization of Marijuana for recreational use in the state of Washington.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Themed after cannabis strains, this laser-cut case comes in 'Sativa' green or 'Indica' black with the 'Hempfest' logo proudly etched in the center. It makes for a great conversation starter :)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We built the Minitux for our customers who want the elegance of our larger &lt;a href="/nwazet-pi-tuxedo-case"&gt;Tuxedo case&lt;/a&gt; but need a smaller format that remains as close as possible to the Pi board.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This beautiful laser-cut acrylic case is designed to give a close fit to a Raspberry Pi model A or B while giving easy access to all of the Pi's connectors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Generously sized vents will make sure your Pi gets the air it needs to stay cool. A slot on the front wall makes it possible to let a &lt;a href="/pi-gpio-ribbon"&gt;GPIO cable&lt;/a&gt; through and thus extend and hack the system. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Minitux case fits perfectly around our &lt;a href="/pi-mcmonster"&gt;Crafty Pi Monster prototyping board&lt;/a&gt;, making it an ideal choice as a generic enclosure for building clean-looking custom projects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The back of the case has two holes designed to fit the VESA 75 specification, making it easy to mount your Pi on the back of a monitor or small TV. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Like the original &lt;a href="/nwazet-pi-tuxedo-case"&gt;Tuxedo case&lt;/a&gt;, it has been quasi-scientifically proven to pass the 'Living Room Aesthetics Test' 99.99% of the time (a.k.a 'The Spouse Test') ;-)&lt;/p&gt;

